(
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FE8ED9CAFE14FA7D" box="[273,406,1455,1481]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 16–21" captionStart-1="FIGURES 22–24" captionStart-2="FIGURES 25–28" captionStart-3="FIGURES 29–31" captionStart-4="FIGURE 32" captionStartId-0="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionStartId-1="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionStartId-2="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionStartId-3="11.[264,383,1595,1619]" captionStartId-4="12.[264,368,1409,1433]" captionTargetBox-0="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetBox-1="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetBox-2="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetBox-3="[321,1245,324,1564]" captionTargetBox-4="[264,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetId-0="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetId-1="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetId-2="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetId-3="figure-66@11.[299,1289,306,1592]" captionTargetId-4="figure-141@12.[66,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="11" captionTargetPageId-4="12" captionText-0="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." captionText-1="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." captionText-2="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." captionText-3="FIGURES 29–31. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 29. Pupal terminal segments (dorsal). 30. Larval spatula and associated papillae. 31. Larval terminal segments." captionText-4="FIGURE 32. Galls of Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. on Bauhinia brevipes." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051099" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051103" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5051099/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5051103/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Figs.16–32</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE7CFFA5FE97D99BFCE0FEEA" blockId="6.[264,1324,1534,1881]" lastBlockId="7.[264,1321,284,350]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7CFFA4FE97D99BFED5F9AC" bold="true" box="[264,343,1534,1560]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Adult.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE7CFFA4FD98D99AFD1AF9AD" box="[519,664,1535,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.3 mm</quantity>
in male (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7CFFA4FC8FD99AFC9DF9AC" box="[784,799,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">n</emphasis>
= 5); 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE7CFFA4FCF0D99AFB8FF9AD" box="[879,1037,1535,1561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.425" metricValueMax="2.45" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.425" valueMax="2.45" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.45 mm</quantity>
in female (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7CFFA4FB02D99AFB2EF9AC" box="[1181,1196,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">n</emphasis>
= 2, from vertex to posterior margin of tergite 8). Head (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FCB6DA42FC3BF9F5" box="[809,953,1575,1601]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Figs. 16, 17</figureCitation>
): Eye facets hexagonal, closely appressed. Antenna with scape cylindrical, elongate, setose, pedicel globose, setose, male and female flagellomeres cylindrical, flagellomere necks short and bare. Male flagellomeres 9–12 subequal in length (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FD43DAFAFCB6F90D" box="[732,820,1695,1721]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); female flagellomeres 9–12 progressively and conspicuously shortened (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FDE6DAA2FD56F955" box="[633,724,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Flagellomeres 1 and 2 not connate. Circumfila sinuous in male (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FE4BDA8AFDA9F8BD" box="[468,555,1775,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) and linear in female (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE7CFFA4FCA4DA8AFC16F8BD" box="[827,916,1775,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-76@7.[284,1326,392,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 16. Male head (frontal). 17. Female head (frontal). 18. Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 19. Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 20. Male antennal flagellomere 5. 21. Female antennal flagellomere 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus with 14–16 setae. Labrum long­attenuate with 2 pairs of ventral sensory setae. Hypopharynx of same shape as labrum, with long, anteriorly directed lateral setulae. Labella hemispherical, each with several lateral setae and 2 pairs of short mesal sensory setae. Palpus with 4 setose segments: first segment globose, others cylindrical.
</paragraph>
<caption id="47817C80BE7DFFA5FE97DA9EFC12F8EC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051091" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5051091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051091/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" startId="7.[264,383,1787,1811]" targetBox="[301,1286,401,1771]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="13412C08BE7DFFA5FE97DA9EFC12F8EC" blockId="7.[264,1323,1787,1880]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FE97DA9EFE51F8A7" bold="true" box="[264,467,1787,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">FIGURES 16–21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE7DFFA5FE40DA99FC84F8A7" authority="Maia &amp; Fernandes, 2005" authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[479,774,1788,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FE40DA99FC84F8A7" box="[479,774,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Schizomyia macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3AB94D61BE7DFFA5FC8EDA99FCCDF8A7" box="[785,847,1788,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FCC5DA9EFCF9F8A7" bold="true" box="[858,891,1787,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">16.</emphasis>
Male head (frontal). 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FBEDDA9EFB11F8A7" bold="true" box="[1138,1171,1787,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">17.</emphasis>
Female head (frontal). 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FEF0DB7BFE12F882" bold="true" box="[367,400,1822,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">18.</emphasis>
Male antennal flagellomeres 9­12. 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FC8EDB7BFCB0F882" bold="true" box="[785,818,1822,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">19.</emphasis>
Female antennal flagellomeres 8­12. 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FB54DB7BFB6EF882" bold="true" box="[1227,1260,1822,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">20.</emphasis>
Male antennal flagellomere 5. 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE7DFFA5FD8EDB25FDB0F8EC" bold="true" box="[529,562,1856,1880]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">21.</emphasis>
Female antennal flagellomere 5.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE72FFAAFEA7DD79FDBCFE1A" blockId="8.[264,1324,284,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Thorax: Anepimeron setose, other pleural sclerites asetose. Wing length (from arculus to apex): 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE72FFAAFEE8DD21FDA2FEEA" box="[375,544,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.525" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.525" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.45">1.45–1.60 mm</quantity>
in male (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE72FFAAFD0FDD21FD1DFEE9" box="[656,671,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">n</emphasis>
= 5); 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE72FFAAFD7ADD21FCBDFEEA" box="[741,831,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
in female (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE72FFAAFC5BDD21FC51FEE9" box="[964,979,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">n</emphasis>
= 2). First tarsomere without apical spur. Tarsal claws simple, bent beyond midlength; empodia well developed, as long as bend in claws (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE72FFAAFE46DDF1FDB3FE1A" box="[473,561,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="47817C80BE72FFAAFE97DB6BFE4EF8DF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" startId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" targetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" targetPageId="8">
