</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE73FFABFEA7DD79FD7EFD2A" blockId="9.[264,1324,284,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
Abdomen. Male (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE73FFABFD90DD79FDEEFE82" box="[527,620,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
): tergites 1–7 rectangular with complete row of posterior setae, several lateral setae, 2 basal trichoid sensilla and elsewhere with scattered scales. Tergite 8 linear with only 2 trichoid sensilla as vestiture. Sternites 2–7 rectangular with setae more abundant at midlength, complete row of posterior setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla; sternite 8 ovoid with several scattered setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla. Female (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE73FFABFE8EDD81FEF2FE4A" box="[273,368,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–24" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[362,1285,494,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[295,1292,470,1801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22–24. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 22. Female midtarsal claw and empodium (lateral). 23. Male abdominal segment 5 to end (dorsolateral). 24. Female abdominal segment 6 to end (dorsolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051093/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
): tergites 1–6 as in male; tergite 7 rectangular with setae more abundant at midlength, complete row of posterior setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla; tergite 8 notched laterally with only 2 basal trichoid sensilla as vestiture. Sternites 2–6 as in male. Sternite 7 much longer than preceding sternite, with rounded margins, scattered setae and 2 basal trichoid sensilla. Sternite 8 not sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<caption id="47817C80BE73FFABFE97DB54FBDEF8DF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" startId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" targetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="13412C08BE73FFABFE97DB54FBDEF8DF" blockId="9.[264,1322,1841,1900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFE97DB54FE56F8FD" bold="true" box="[264,468,1841,1865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">FIGURES 25–28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE73FFABFE7EDB57FC8AF8FD" authority="Maia &amp; Fernandes, 2005" authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[481,776,1842,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFE7EDB57FC8AF8FD" box="[481,776,1842,1865]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Schizomyia macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3AB94D61BE73FFABFC8BDB57FCD1F8FD" box="[788,851,1842,1865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFCC0DB54FC03F8FD" bold="true" box="[863,897,1841,1865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">25.</emphasis>
Male terminalia (dorsal). 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFB31DB54FB52F8FD" bold="true" box="[1198,1232,1841,1865]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">26.</emphasis>
Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFD93DB31FDAFF8D8" bold="true" box="[524,557,1876,1900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">27.</emphasis>
Pupal head (frontal). 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE73FFABFC89DB31FCB5F8D8" bold="true" box="[790,823,1876,1900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">28.</emphasis>
Pupal prothoracic spiracle.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7DD79FD9AFE1A" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FD9EDD79FDDAFE82" box="[513,600,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
): gonocoxites narrow and setose, with apical lobe; gonostylus short cylindrical and setose; cercus reniform, completely separate and setose; hypoproct bilobed and setose; parameres present; aedeagus triangular, tapering gradually toward apex, rounded apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7DDD9FB94FE4A" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
Ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FE59DDD9FD9FFE62" box="[454,541,444,470]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) protrusible, 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FD23DDD9FC94FE62" box="[700,790,444,470]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long (from distal margin of tergite 7 to end), (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FE8DDD81FEA3FE49" box="[274,289,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 1), needle part 1.9 as long as sternite 7. Cercus distinct, fused.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7DE6EFEDBFCD2" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FEA7DE6EFE02FD91" bold="true" box="[312,384,523,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Pupa.</emphasis>
Color: pale. Length: 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FD05DE69FCAFFD92" box="[666,813,524,550]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.0999999999999996" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.3 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FCD8DE69FCD4FD91" box="[839,854,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 4). Head (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FB97DE69FBEAFD92" box="[1032,1128,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
): antennal base thickened; cephalic seta 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FDB1DE51FD4EFDFA" box="[558,716,564,590]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.095" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.1 mm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FC82DE51FCAEFDF9" box="[797,812,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 4); face without horns; 2 pairs of lower facial papillae (1 pair asetose and other pair with seta 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FC15DE39FBB4FDC2" box="[906,1078,604,630]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.07" valueMax="0.08" valueMin="0.06">0.06–0.08 mm</quantity>
long, 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FB1DDE39FB13FDC1" box="[1154,1169,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 4); 3 pairs of lateral facial papillae (1 pair with seta 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FC8FDEE1FC0FFD2A" box="[784,909,644,670]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.005">0.005 mm</quantity>
long and 2 pairs asetose). Upper cephalic margin thickened laterally. Thorax: prothoracic spiracle digitiform, elongate and slightly curved, 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FE55DEB1FDF4FD5A" box="[458,630,724,750]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.075" valueMax="0.09" valueMin="0.06">0.06–0.09 mm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FD59DEB1FD57FD59" box="[710,725,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 4) (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FCBDDEB1FCF9FD5A" box="[802,891,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="9.[264,383,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[368,1176,734,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-176@9.[291,1280,704,1842]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 25. Male terminalia (dorsal). 26. Female tergite 8 and ovipositor. 27. Pupal head (frontal). 28. Pupal prothoracic spiracle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051097/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FB88DEB1FBF0FD5A" box="[1047,1138,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–31" captionStartId="11.[264,383,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[321,1245,324,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-66@11.[299,1289,306,1592]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–31. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 29. Pupal terminal segments (dorsal). 30. Larval spatula and associated papillae. 31. Larval terminal segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051099" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051099/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): segments 2–7 with several conspicuous dorsal spines and anteriorly to them, several short spines and many spinules; segment 8 with shorter dorsal spines and spinules; segment 9 without spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7DF11FEB4FBE2" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FEA7DF11FE09FC3A" bold="true" box="[312,395,884,910]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Larva.</emphasis>
Body elongate cylindrical and tapered at both ends. Color: yellow. Length: 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FA9BDF11FEB7FC02" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FED8DFF9FED4FC01" box="[327,342,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">n</emphasis>
= 1). Integument rough. Spatula with 2 well­developed teeth and long stalk; sternal papillae setose; 3 pairs of lateral papillae on each side of spatula (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FB99DFA1FBD6FC6A" box="[1030,1108,964,990]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–31" captionStartId="11.[264,383,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[321,1245,324,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-66@11.[299,1289,306,1592]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–31. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 29. Pupal terminal segments (dorsal). 30. Larval spatula and associated papillae. 31. Larval terminal segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051099" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051099/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig.30</figureCitation>
) (2 pairs setose, 1 pair asetose). Abdominal segment 8 with medial projection bearing pair of papillae setose; terminal segment convex, with 4 pairs of papillae (1 pair corniform, 3 pairs setiform) (
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FB66D871FEAAFBE2" captionStart="FIGURES 29–31" captionStartId="11.[264,383,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[321,1245,324,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-66@11.[299,1289,306,1592]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–31. Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. 29. Pupal terminal segments (dorsal). 30. Larval spatula and associated papillae. 31. Larval terminal segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051099" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051099/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7D801FA8AFB42" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FEA7D801FEEFFBCA" bold="true" box="[312,365,1124,1150]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Gall</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="8BC5308DBE70FFA8FE1FD801FE59FBCA" box="[384,475,1124,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="12.[264,368,1409,1433]" captionTargetBox="[264,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-141@12.[66,1313,449,1384]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 32. Galls of Schizomyia macrocapillata sp. n. on Bauhinia brevipes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051103/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). The spherical gall is on the adaxial leaf surface, has a cover of long orange to reddish hairs, and is single chambered. A single larva is found inside the gall. At the beginning of gall formation, the trichomes are whitish­pinkish but change color as the gall matures. When exposed directly to sunlight, the trichomes become reddish­orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
