<subSubSection id="5BE47F83BE70FFA8FEA7D9C1FC63FA52" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7D9C1FC63FA52" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FEA7D9C1FE46FA0A" bold="true" box="[312,452,1444,1470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE70FFA8FDD7D9C1FD78FA09" authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[584,762,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FDD7D9C1FD78FA09" box="[584,762,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FC25D9C1FB8DFA09" box="[954,1039,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">makros</emphasis>
(long) + 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FBE1D9C1FB59FA09" box="[1150,1243,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">capillus</emphasis>
(hair), and refers to the presence of the long hairs on the gall surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5BE47F83BE70FFA8FEA7D991FEFAF892" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="13412C08BE70FFA8FEA7D991FEFAF892" blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FEA7D991FE33F9BA" bold="true" box="[312,433,1524,1550]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE70FFA8FE24D991FD7FF9B9" authorityName="Maia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2005" box="[443,765,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocapillata">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FE24D991FD7FF9B9" box="[443,765,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Schizomyia macrocapillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE70FFA8FB3AD991FEDDF982" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FB3AD991FAA8F9B9" box="[1189,1322,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Schizomyia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, mainly due to the presence of a distinct female cercus. Additionally, male tergite 8 is linear and asetose with two trichoid sensilla, the ovipositor is 
<quantity id="D40681EDBE70FFA8FC6BDA21FBCFF9EA" box="[1012,1101,1604,1630]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long, the larva has setose sternal papillae, and the pupa has the antennal base thickened. Previous studies on these galls identified the gall­inducing insect as 
<taxonomicName id="D4FE578BBE70FFA8FCFFDAF1FC62F919" box="[864,992,1684,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Contarinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FCFFDAF1FC62F919" box="[864,992,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Contarinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="776F51F9BE70FFA8FC6ADAF1FAA4F91A" author="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Price P. W." box="[1013,1318,1684,1710]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="14 - 20" refId="ref3821" refString="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Price P. W. (1992) The adaptive significance of insect gall distribution: survivorship of species in xeric and mesic habitats. Oecologia, 90, 14 - 20." type="journal article" year="1992">Fernandes &amp; Price 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="776F51F9BE70FFA8FE97DAD9FDBDF962" author="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Madeira, B. G. &amp; Allain, L. R. &amp; Lara, A. C. F. &amp; Araujo, L. M. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[264,575,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="285 - 288" refId="ref3534" refString="Cornelissen T. G., Madeira, B. G., Allain, L. R., Lara, A. C. F., Araujo, L. M., Fernandes, G. W. (1997) Multiple responses of insect herbivores to plant vigor. Ciencia &amp; Cultura, 49, 285 - 288." type="journal article" year="1997">
Cornelissen 
<emphasis id="218AF01ABE70FFA8FE39DAD9FE6CF961" box="[422,494,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="776F51F9BE70FFA8FDC7DAD9FD14F962" author="Cornelissen T. G. &amp; Negreiros, D. &amp; Fernandes, G. W." box="[600,662,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="135 - 150" refId="ref3598" refString="Cornelissen T. G., Negreiros, D. &amp; Fernandes, G. W. (2002) Plant resistance against gall-forming insects: the role of hypersensitivity. In: Wagner, M. (Ed.), Mechanisms and Deployment of Resistance in Trees to Insects. Kluwer Academic Press, pp. 135 - 150." type="book chapter" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="776F51F9BE70FFA8FD30DAD9FBC1F962" author="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Cornelissen, T. G." box="[687,1091,1724,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" pagination="144 - 152" refId="ref3739" refString="Fernandes G. W. &amp; Cornelissen, T. G. (1997) Plant hypersensitivity against tissue invasive insects: Bauhinia brevipes and Contarinia sp. interaction. In: Czoka, Y., Price, P. W., Mattson, W. J. (Eds.), The Biology of Gall Arthropods. United States Department of Agriculture, General Technical Report NC- 199, North Carolina, pp. 144 - 152." type="book chapter" year="1997">Fernandes &amp; Cornelissen 1997</bibRefCitation>
